txt.en: 'While we seek a living prisoner, I have little sympathy for Men who ally themselves with the spiders, an ancient enemy of my people. Do not spare any who refuse to surrender to you.'
Legolas has asked you to thin the ranks of the Ungoledain at Cadar Skûs.
'While we seek a living prisoner, I have little sympathy for Men who ally themselves with the spiders, an ancient enemy of my people. Do not spare any who refuse to surrender to you.'
'I am always impressed by your skills in battle, [placeholder]. We have done well thinning their numbers.'
Many Ungoledain have been defeated this day.\n\nYou should talk to Legolas.
Unoledain have set up camp in Cadar Skûs, a small village in western Cirith Ungol.\n\nYou should defeat Ungoledain in Cadar Skûs.
